9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 779, L.D. 1174, “An Act to Allow Gun
10 Shops to Hold Firearms for Veterans of the United States Armed Forces and First
11 Responders”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Limit the Liability of Gun Shops That Provide Firearm Hold Agreements'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 1 in paragraph B in the first line
15 (page 1, line 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or oral"
16 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 1 by striking out all of paragraph C
17 (page 1, lines 11 and 12 in L.D.).
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 1 by relettering the paragraphs to
19 read alphabetically.
20 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines
21 14 to 22 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
22 '2. Holding firearms for 3rd parties. A gun shop may take possession of a firearm
23 from a person for safekeeping under the following conditions:
24 A. The gun shop enters into a firearm hold agreement with the owner of the firearm;
25 and
26 B. The gun shop contacts the owner of the firearm every 6 months after taking
27 possession of the firearm until the firearm is returned to the owner of the firearm.'
28 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 3 in the last line (page 1, line 27 in
29 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "section." the following: 'An action may not be
30 brought against a person for refusing to enter into a firearm hold agreement with any
31 person.'
32 Amend the bill in section 2 in the 3rd and 4th lines (page 1, lines 33 and 34 in L.D.) by
33 striking out the following: "for veterans of the United States Armed Forces or first
