5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment removes the limitation in the bill that a firearm hold agreement may
77 be made only with a veteran of the United States Armed Forces or a first responder. The
88 amendment clarifies that a firearm hold agreement must be written and that held firearms
99 do not need to be kept separate from the gun shop's inventory. The amendment prohibits
1100 an action from being brought against a person for refusing to enter into a firearm hold
1111 agreement. The amendment also changes the title of the bill.
